{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 4.4.2 Benefits of Victory\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 Just as PCs who suffer defeat can suffer ongoing ill effects in addition to the loss of the prize at hand, PCs who win can gain extra benefits of victory.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 The PC gets a bonus on the selected abilities, or in the specified situation, as determined by their victory level. The bonus remains until the PC suffers a defeat on a contest using either the bonus or the ability with which they won the original contest. A PC can\u8217't decline the bonus because they might lose it; they must always use it in any contest in which it ought, in the GM\u8217's judgment, to apply.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 At the end of a storyline, especially when a significant period of game-world time passes between the conclusion of one episode and the beginning of the next, the GM may declare that all benefits of victory have expired.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A PC may apply bonuses from multiple benefits to a single contest.\par}
