{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs32 5.2 Group Simple Contest\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 In the group simple contest, multiple participants take part in a simple contest. Each of the participants conducts an individual simple contest, and the results for each side are collated to determine the victor.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 A group simple contest may pit all of the participating PCs against a single resistance, representing one obstacle. Alternatively, a group simple contest may be a series of paired match-ups between two groups of contestants. PCs forced to participate in more than one contest face the standard multiple opponent penalties.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa180 \li0 \fi0 \b \fs28 5.2.1 Procedure\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab Frame the contest.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab Figure each PC\u8217's target number (TN) using the ability rating and any modifiers. The PCs TN is the rating of their ability, plus or minus modifiers the GM may give the PC.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 3.\tx360\tab The GM determines the resistance. The GM opposes the PC with a resistance\u8212-the harder the task or tougher the opponent, the higher the resistance.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 4.\tx360\tab For each PC, Roll a d20 to determine the PCs degree of success or failure, then apply any bumps. The GM does the same for the resistance. Compare your rolled number with your TN to see how well you succeeded or failed with your ability. Remember to apply any bumps from masteries or hero points.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 5.\tx360\tab Determine the number of RPs scored by the victor in the contest from the Group Simple Contest Results table. On a tie the victory goes to the Better Roll.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 6.\tx360\tab Sum the RPs gained for each side.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 7.\tx360\tab The side with the highest number of RP is the victor in the contest.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 1.\tx360\tab [Option] Determine Degee of Succes based on the difference between the winner and loser\u8217's resource point totals on the Group Simple Contest results table.\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li720 \fi-360 2.\tx360\tab [Option] Determine Benefits of Victory or Consequences of Defeat.\sa180\par}
{\pard \ql \f0 \sa0 \li360 \fi-360 8.\tx360\tab Describe the result based on the agreed prize.\sa180\par}
